2005 Nike Considered BB Low

Size: US10.5/ UK9.5/ EU44.5/ 28.5 cm

Condition: Gently used

The Considered BB is a shoe inspired by iconic Nike silhouettes, retooled for better product performance & environmental sustainability. The BB borrows elements of the Dunk, Blazer, and Free run. The latter of which was Nikes latest technical innovation at the time. The shoes are crafted with vegetable tanned leather with no interior lining. The uppers are fully stitched to the soles, resulting in a product that is made without the use of adhesives or toxic chemicals. Created by veteran footwear designer Andreas Harlow @andreasharlow

Link in bio.

Nike ACG Considered Mules

Size: US7.5W/ UK5/ EU38.5/ 24.5 cm

Condition: Gently used

Rare mules from the acclaimed Nike Considered lineup. Made with vegetable tanned leather with no lining, fully stitched to the soles. Cnstructed without the use of adhesives or toxic chemicals.

This model has a lot in common with the classic Nike Dunk, butÂ with ACG & Nike Considered for improved product performance and environmental sustainability.

The 'lizard' pattern on the soles maximizes the sticky rock climbing rubber surface area. At the same time, the grooves make it easier for water to escape. This prevents hydroplaning & improves traction. The outsole graphic is simple but memorable.

Link in bio.

2005 Nike Considered Blazer

Size: US8/ UK7/ EU41/ 26 cm

Condition: Gently used

The Considered Blazer is a reinterpretation of the classic Blazer Mid with Nike Considered for product performance and environmental sustainability. The uppers are made with vegetable tanned leather with hemp textiles on the vamp & tongue. They also feature Nike Free soles that are fully stitched to the upper without the use of adhesives or toxic chemicals. Overall, a very comfortable & flexible shoe made with high-quality materials.

Link in bio.

2005 Nike Considered Boot

Size: US9/ UK8/ EU42.5/ 27 cm

Colorway: Baroque Brown/ Iron

Condition: Gently used

The Considered Boot is the flagship model of the acclaimed Nike Considered line. These special boots are made by hand with vegetable tanned leather and a tightly woven hemp shoe lace system. Creating a beautifully unique moccasin-style chukka boot.

The soles utilize a snap together fit system that is sewn directly to the uppers, eliminating the use of adhesives or toxic chemicals.
Designed by Steve McDonald @mcsteve

This silhouette is based on the Nike Zoom Air Huarache 2k5 basketball shoe. Instead, it is made from vegetable tanned leather and woven hemp. They also feature an exposed wooden heel counter, something you just won't see on other Nike products. Constructed without the use of adhesives or toxic chemicals.

TECHNOLOGY
What makes HyVentâ„¢ DT different is the interior microgrid print. Lighter in weight and more efficient than a liner or laminated inner layer, this treatment is so minimal that we refer to it as a half-layer. The microgrid half-layer physically separates the fabricâ€™s waterproof barrier from the skin. This separation:

Prevents the clammy feeling of coating on skin
Increases air circulation and ventilation
Helps channel moisture away from the skin so it can evaporate
Allows the garment to move more freely over other layers

Progressing through the 20th century, Carhartt achieved an expansive manufacturing and distribution footprint, furnishing steadfast, meticulously fashioned attire for multifarious industries and undertakings, encompassing pursuits such as hunting, agriculture, construction, and even wartime endeavors during WWI and WWII.

Demonstrating a propensity for innovation, Carhartt diversified its repertoire during the 1960s, venturing into sports apparel, casual outerwear, and jeans. This culminated in 1989, as Carhartt celebrated a centenary of existence as a venerated force in the domain of workwear.

Renzo Rosso, the visionary behind the Diesel brand, established in 1978, embarked on a transformative journey from the unlikeliest of origins in Molvena, a quaint town nestled in northeastern Italy. With an unwavering commitment to cultural innovation, Diesel has consistently emerged as a trailblazer, employing creative subversion to amplify narratives that hold contemporary significance.

Renzo's formative years were spent attending a nearby technical school, where he delved into the intricacies of textile design and garment construction. Fueling his passion for creation, he fearlessly embarked on experiments with his mother's sewing machine, ingeniously adapting existing products.

An anecdote of particular intrigue tells of a friend presenting Renzo with a pair of American jeans, which he deftly transformed into a striking bell-bottom design. This marked the genesis of Renzo's foray into the realm of apparel.

During his tenure at Goldschmidt, a prestigious denim brand, Adriano Goldschmidt astutely recognized Renzo's innate talent. United by their shared vision, the dynamic duo forged Diesel in 1978, providing a vessel for Renzo's boundless creativity and relentless drive. In doing so, they catapulted Diesel into the echelons of authenticity within the fashion world, effortlessly embracing contemporary trends while maintaining a timeless allure.

For Autumn Winter 23 Griffin have partnered with Pertex again. The fabric was first used for  Nims #14peaks mountaineering suit that we designed here at Griffin Studio. 
Pertex fabric is a strong water resistant rip stop made to endure all the elements and features on the iconic Griffin Sleeping bag Coat, Atlantic Parka, USMC jacket, Hooded running vest and Griffin Overshirt. 
 
Pertex, first registered in 1979 Lancashire , England . Pertex have grown from humble beginnings as a simple vision into a iconic technical fabric brand.
